  "text": "The multi-rater, 360 • feature is a key element of the study design as it increases the accuracy of results and avoids common method bias. Multi-rater perceptions were used to measure the leadership effectiveness of the next-generation leaders in the study, as self-ratings are often unreliable and inflated [CITATION_1] ). In addition, using different sources to assess key measures is the best ex ante procedure to avoid potential common method variance [CITATION_2] .",
